[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Research has shown that for children between the ages of seven to 16, 
[normal]the involveme
[normal]nt of parents
[normal] 
[normal]in their schooling had a greater influence on attainment than family background, size of family and level of 
[normal]parental education
[normal]. 
[normal]Parental engagement with their child’s education can 
[normal]have 
[normal]a real impact on attainment
[normal],
[normal] and a parent’s attitude to school, often based on their own experiences of education, can also significantly affect their child’s attitude
[normal] and subsequent achievement
[normal]. 
